2013 8th<ref name=\"Andriy SHEVCHENKO - Dynamo Kyiv and Ukraine\" />\n*2004 \u2013 3rd<ref name=\"Andriy SHEVCHENKO - Dynamo Kyiv and Ukraine\" />\n*Decade \u2013 13th<ref name=\"Andriy SHEVCHENKO - Dynamo Kyiv and Ukraine\" />\n\n===Records===\n*[[Supercoppa Italiana#All-time top goalscorers|Supercoppa Italiana second-highest all-time top scorer]] with 3 goals, alongside [[Alessandro Del Piero]], [[Samuel Eto'o]], and [[Carlos Tevez]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/alltime_goalgetter/ita-supercoppa/tore/1/|title=All-time top goalscorers|publisher=worldfootball.net}}</ref><ref name=myjuve.it>{{cite web|url=http://www.myjuve.it/statistiche-giocatori-juventus/classifica-reti_segnate-supercoppa_italiana-SI.aspx|title=Juventus F.C. Giocatori, Statistiche: Reti nella Supercoppa Italiana|publisher=My Juve.it|language=Italian|accessdate=21 January 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Ukraine national football team#Top Ukraine goalscorers|Ukraine national team all-time top scorer]] with 48 goals.\n*[[Derby della Madonnina#Top Goal scorers|''Derby della Madonnina'' all-time top scorer]] with 14 goals.\n*All-time AC Milan top scorer in Champions League with 33 goals.\n*All-time [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] (UEFA) top scorer with 26 goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fr.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminarydraw/news/newsid=1479808/index.html|title=Les qualifs en chiffres|publisher=FIFA|date=26 July 2011|accessdate=15 December 2011|language=fr}}</ref>\n*[[Oleh Blokhin club|Top scorer in the history of Ukrainian football with 374 goals]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of men's footballers with 100 or more international caps]]\n* [[List of top international men's association football goal scorers by country]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n* {{UEFA player}}\n* {{Soccerbase}}\n* {{FFU player}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n*[http://thetopforward.com/view?id=13 Andriy Shevchenko] at Topforward\n\n{{Current managers of UEFA national teams}}\n{{Nav