League|1999]]\n*[[Ukrainian Cup]] (3): [[1996 Ukrainian Cup Final|1995\u201396]], [[1998 Ukrainian Cup Final|1997\u201398]], [[1998\u201399 Ukrainian Cup|1998\u201399]]\n*[[Ukrainian Super Cup]]: [[Ukrainian Super Cup|2011]]\n*[[CIS Cup]] (3): [[CIS Cup|1996]], [[CIS Cup|1997]], [[CIS Cup|1998]]\n\n'''[[A.C. Milan|Milan]]'''\n*[[Serie A]]: [[2003\u201304 Serie A|2003\u201304]]\n*[[Coppa Italia]]: [[2002\u201303 Coppa Italia|2002\u201303]]\n*[[Supercoppa Italiana]]: [[2004 Supercoppa Italiana|2004]]\n*[[UEFA Champions League]]: [[2002\u201303 UEFA Champions League|2002\u201303]]; Runner-up [[2004\u201305 UEFA Champions League|2004\u201305]]\n*[[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[2003 UEFA Super Cup|2003]]\n\n'''[[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]'''\n*[[EFL Cup|Football League Cup]]: [[2006\u201307 Football League Cup|2006\u201307]]\n*[[FA Cup]]: [[2006\u201307 FA Cup|2006\u201307]]\n*[[UEFA Champions League]] Runner-up: [[2007\u201308 UEFA Champions League|2007\u201308]]\n\n===Individual===\n*[[Ballon d'Or]]: [[2004 Ballon d'Or|2004]]; Third place: 1999, 2000\n*[[2004 FIFA World Player of the Year]]: Bronze Award \n*[[Ukrainian Footballer of the Year]]: (6) 1997, 1999, 2000, 2001, 2004, 2005\n*Ukrainian Sports 1999.<ref name=\"Andriy SHEVCHENKO - Dynamo Kyiv and Ukraine\">{{cite web|author=Kartmann|url=http://www.espacefoot.net/shevchenko.htm |title=Andriy Shevchenko \u2013 Dynamo Kyiv and Ukraine|publisher=Espacefoot.net|date=29 September 1976|accessdate=15 December 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111123012416/http://www.espacefoot.net/shevchenko.htm|archivedate=23 November 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n*[[Commonwealth of Independent States Cup#Top scorers by year|Commonwealth of Independent States Cup Top Scorer]]: 1997\n*Commonwealth of Independent States [[CIS Cup|1997]] Team of the competition<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/cis97.html|title=Commonwealth of Independent States Cup 1997|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]]|date=25 November 1999|accessdate=8 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ukrainian Premier League|Ukrainian Premier League Top Scorer]]: 1998\u201399\n*[[Vyscha Liha Footballer of the Year|Ukrainian Premier League Player of the Year]]: 1997\n*[[Ukrainian Cup|Ukrainian Cup Top Scorer]] (2): [[1994\u201395 Ukrainian Cup#Top goalscorers|1994\u201395]], [[1997\u201398 Ukrainian Cup|1997\u201398]]\n*[[European Sports Magazines|ESM Team of the Year]]: (3) [[European Sports Magazines#1999\u20132000|1999\u201300]], [[European Sports Magazines#2003\u201304|2003\u201304]], [[European Sports Magazines#2004\u201305|2004\u201305]]\n*[[List of European Cup and UEFA Champions League top scorers#European Cup and UEFA Champions League top goalscorer by seasons|UEFA Champions League Top Scorer]]: (2) [[1998\u201399 UEFA Champions League|1998\u201399]], [[2005\u201306 UEFA Champions League|2005\u201306]]\n*[[UEFA Club Football Awards#Best Forward|UEFA Club Forward of the Year]]: 1998\u201399\n*[[UEFA Team of the Year]]: (2) [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2004|2004]], [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2005|2005]]\n*[[UEFA Super Cup]] Man of the Match: [[2003 UEFA Super Cup|2003]]\n*[[Serie A Foreign Footballer of the Year]]: 2000\n*[[Oscar del Calcio#Serie A Goal of the Year|Serie A Goal of the Year]]: 2004.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acmilan.com/it/news/show_photo/1/951|title=GLI OSCAR DEL CALCIO: SHEVA AUTORE DEL GOL PIU' BELLO|publisher=AC Milan|date=25 January 2005|language=it|accessdate=15 December 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120523184344/http://www.acmilan.com/it/news/show_photo/1/951|archivedate=23 May 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n*[[Football records in Italy#Top scorers (capocannonieri) by season|Serie A Top Scorer]]: (2) [[1999\u20132000 Serie A|1999\u201300]], [[2003\u201304 Serie A|2003\u201304]]\n*Best Player of Eastern Europe \u2013 Focus Vest magazine Trophy: 2001\n*[[Footballer of the Year in Baltic and Commonwealth of Independent States (Sport-Express)|Baltic and Commonwealth of Independent States Footballer of the Year]]: (2) 2004, 2005\n*[[Golden Foot award]] : 2005\n*[[FIFPro World XI]]: 2005\n*[[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification|FIFA World Cup qualification 2002]] top scoring European with 10 goals.\n*[[FIFA 100]]\n*[[Sport Movies & TV - Milano International FICTS Fest|Excellence Guirlande D'Honneur]] by the [[FICTS (F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale Cin\u00e9ma T\u00e9l\u00e9vision Sportifs)|FICTS]].\n*The World Team of the Decade by Mirror Football: 2009<ref>{{cite web|title=The World Team of the Decade, as selected by John Cross|url=http://www.mirrorfootball.co.uk/opinion/blogs/mirror-football-blog/The-World-Team-of-the-Decade-as-selected-by-John-Cross-article257875.html|publisher=[[Mirror Football]]|date=31 December 2009|accessdate=31 December 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091218104232/http://www.mirrorfootball.co.uk/opinion/blogs/mirror-football-blog/The-World-Team-of-the-Decade-as-selected-by-John-Cross-article257875.html|archivedate=18 December 2009|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n*[[A.C. Milan]] Hall of Fame.<ref name=\"A.C. Milan Hall of Fame\">{{cite web|url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/andriy-shevchenko|title=Hall of Fame|publisher=AC Milan|accessdate=8 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[List of footballers with 100 or more caps|UEFA awards 100 caps]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fr.uefa.com/memberassociations/news/newsid=1671087.html|publisher=Fr.uefa.com|language=fr|date=11 October 2011|accessdate=8 November 2019|title=R\u00e9compense UEFA pour les 'centenaires'}}</ref>\n*[[Pallone d'Argento]] 2003\u201304.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ussi.it/2016/a-florenzi-il-pallone-dargento-coppa-giaime-fiumano/|title=A Florenzi il \"Pallone d\u2019Argento\" Coppa Giaim\u00e8 Fiumano|publisher=ussi.it|language=it|date=8 May 2016|accessdate=8 November 2019}}</ref>\n*''[[L'\u00c9quipe]]'' Team of the Year: (2) 2004, 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2004/dicembre/27/Equipe_sceglie_italiani__ga_10_0412276678.shtml|title=Ultime notizie sportive \u2013 La Gazzetta dello Sport|publisher=Archiviostorico.gazzetta.it|date=27 December 2004|language=it|accessdate=8 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ultime notizie sportive \u2013 La Gazzetta dello Sport|publisher=Archiviostorico.gazzetta.it|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2005/dicembre/28/Shevchenko_Kaka_Maldini_nell_undici_ga_10_0512285292.shtml|date=28 December 2005|language=it|accessdate=8 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[World Soccer (magazine)#The Greatest Players of the 20th century|''World Soccer'''s 100 Greatest Players of the 20th Century]]\n*Shevchenko has been ranked 18th in the Independent's countdown of the top 100 footballers of the 21st century:2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/century-countdown-100-list-messi-ronaldo-zidane-ronaldinho-a9160546.html|title=The Century: 100-1 countdown featuring Lionel Messi, Cristiano Ronaldo, Ronaldinho and more|author=Brown, Luke|work=[[The Independent]]|date=18 October 2019|accessdate=8 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Ballon d'Or===\n*[[1998 Ballon d'Or|1998]] \u2013 nominated (top 50)\n*[[1999 Ballon d'Or|1999]] \u2013 3rd\n*[[2000 Ballon d'Or|2000]] \u2013 3rd\n*[[2001 Ballon d'Or|2001]] \u2013 8th\n*[[2003 Ballon d'Or|2003]] \u2013 4th\n*[[2004 Ballon d'Or|2004]] \u2013 1st\n*[[2005 Ballon d'Or|2005]] \u2013 6th\n*[[2006 Ballon d'Or|2006]] \u2013 nominated (top 50)\n\n===FIFA World Player of the Year===\n*[[1999 FIFA World Player of the Year|1999]] \u2013 7th\n*[[2000 FIFA World Player of the Year|2000]] \u2013 5th\n*[[2001 FIFA World Player of the Year|2001]] \u2013 9th\n*[[2003 FIFA World Player of the Year|2003]] \u2013 10th\n*[[2004 FIFA World Player of the Year|2004]] \u2013 3rd\n*[[2005 FIFA World Player of the Year|2005]] \u2013 6th\n*[[2006 FIFA World Player of the Year|2006]] \u2013 21st\n\n===World Football Award===\n*1999 \u2013 3rd<ref name=\"Andriy SHEVCHENKO - Dynamo Kyiv and Ukraine\" />\n*2000 \u2013 3rd<ref name=\"Andriy SHEVCHENKO - Dynamo Kyiv and Ukraine\" />\n*2001 \u2013 8th<ref name=\"Andriy SHEVCHENKO - Dynamo Kyiv and Ukraine\"/>\n*2003 \u2013 8th<ref name=\"Andriy SHEVCHENKO - Dynamo Kyiv and Ukraine\" />\n*2004 \u2013 3rd<ref name=\"Andriy SHEVCHENKO - Dynamo Kyiv and Ukraine\" />\n*Decade \u2013 13th<ref name=\"Andriy SHEVCHENKO - Dynamo Kyiv and Ukraine\" />\n\n===Records===\n*[[Supercoppa Italiana#All-time top goalscorers|Supercoppa Italiana second-highest all-time top scorer]] with 3 goals, alongside [[Alessandro Del Piero]], [[Samuel Eto'o]], and [[Carlos Tevez]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/alltime_goalgetter/ita-supercoppa/tore/1/|title=All-time top goalscorers|publisher=worldfootball.net}}</ref><ref name=myjuve.it>{{cite web|url=http://www.myjuve.it/statistiche-giocatori-juventus/classifica-reti_segnate-supercoppa_italiana-SI.aspx|title=Juventus F.C. Giocatori, Statistiche: Reti nella Supercoppa Italiana|publisher=My Juve.it|language=Italian|accessdate=21 January 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Ukraine national football team#Top Ukraine goalscorers|Ukraine national team all-time top scorer]] with 48 goals.\n*[[Derby della Madonnina#Top Goal scorers|''Derby della Madonnina'' all-time top scorer]] with 14 goals.\n*All-time AC Milan top scorer in Champions League with 33 goals.\n*All-time [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] (UEFA) top scorer with 26 goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fr.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminarydraw/news/newsid=1479808/index.html|title=Les qualifs en chiffres|publisher=FIFA|date=26 July 2011|accessdate=15 December 2011|language=fr}}</ref>\n*[[Oleh Blokhin club|Top scorer in the history of Ukrainian football with 374 goals]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of men's footballers with 100 or more international caps]]\n* [[List of top international men's association football goal scorers by country]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n* 